1
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:13,659
How long you gonna be?

2
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:23,737
Be right out,

3
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:26,745
you're a pain!

4
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:53,664
Hey, American.

5
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:55,705
I'm still here, gettin' a manicure.

6
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:59,746
Things okay?

7
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:02,704
Gettin' tanned? Don't get burned!

8
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:05,585
Bruno's here too.

9
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:07,659
You got a crap body!

10
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,779
Is Bruno here?

11
00:03:11,640 --> 00:03:12,698
He's over there.

12
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:21,699
You doin' a lamp?

13
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:29,663
It's 2,000.

14
00:04:29,760 --> 00:04:32,627
How much are you
supposed to get this week?

15
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:33,778
9,200.

16
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:37,586
Sure? It was less last week.

17
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,625
Yes, Don Ciro 9,200.

18
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:44,625
Another 2,000 Euro and we're even.

19
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:47,585
Don Ciro, don't take all day.

20
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:49,545
He's slow.

21
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:52,665
Hurry, so we can go home.

22
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:56,585
Things okay out there?

23
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:57,783
Keep your eyes open.

24
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,737
That's it.

25
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:16,705
Put paper cups in.

26
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:22,783
Toilet paper.

27
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:32,547
- Then, Mom?
- Some shampoo.

28
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:35,743
A mozzarella...

29
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:42,625
Shampoo, not bath oil!

30
00:05:42,760 --> 00:05:45,581
You're rushin' me!

31
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:47,659
And you're drivin' me crazy!

32
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:55,546
Hurry up, there are
more groceries to deliver.

33
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:57,585
- Nothing else?
- No.

34
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:04,706
- Be back later.
- Don't get yourself lost.

35
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:17,785
- Simone.
- Toto, what's up?

36
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:21,586
- What's happening?
- I'm workin'.

37
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:25,740
Know what happened?
They arrested Vitale and Bon Bon.

38
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:27,618
Really?

39
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:30,700
- Got somethin' to eat?
- Yeah, but it's not mine.

40
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:32,665
Bye, see you.

41
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:50,625
Carmela, ma'am!

42
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:57,783
Hi, Boxer.

43
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:26,619
Two doses, two doses!

44
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:29,625
Please, give me a dose!

45
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:36,580
Gaetano, check it!

46
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:11,545
One, two, three...

47
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:16,744
Goodbye.

48
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,745
Don Ciro, be more punctual.

49
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:23,580
I'll pass it on.

50
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:32,658
Eleven and twelve.

51
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:35,579
See if he wants coffee.

52
00:08:35,680 --> 00:08:37,659
No, but thank you anyway...

53
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:39,625
I'll show you out.

54
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:41,580
Have a good day.

55
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:51,586
Four hundred...

56
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:56,778
Five hundred.

57
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:59,659
The same amount again?

58
00:09:00,720 --> 00:09:03,666
I've said a hundred times
I can't manage like this.

59
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,658
Don Carlo...

60
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:12,542
Did you tell them I can't manage
on this chickenfeed?

61
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:15,581
I have to pay rent, lights, water.

62
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:19,541
I can't survive,
I'm strapped with debts.

63
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:22,660
- I'll pass it on.
- You always say that!

64
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:25,541
Are you mockin' me?

65
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:27,743
I don't get it!

66
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:29,743
Listen,

67
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:32,625
I've got a son to support,

68
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:35,666
for forty years
I've kept him off the streets,

69
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:38,625
he's unemployed.

70
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:41,700
What can I do,
go over to the other side?

71
00:09:42,640 --> 00:09:46,588
They know, I served you honestly
for forty years.

72
00:09:46,680 --> 00:09:49,706
My wife's in jail,
is this the thanks we get?

73
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:53,540
Are we crazy?
Do I have to raise hell?

74
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:57,704
Silvana!

75
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:07,546
May I?

76
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:10,778
Come on in!

77
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:12,618
Maria!

78
00:10:14,760 --> 00:10:16,546
The bill?

79
00:10:16,640 --> 00:10:18,699
Talk to Mom.

80
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:26,620
Put this in your pocket.

81
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:28,586
Thank you.

82
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:43,625
Carabinieri on the street!

83
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:55,705
He's comin' out!

84
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:16,547
I'm the best, number one!

85
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:17,743
So?

86
00:11:18,640 --> 00:11:19,664
Go, Marco!

87
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:23,742
- I'll blast these roaches!
- Who do you think you're fighting?

88
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:27,540
I'm number one! Tony Montana!

89
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:29,659
The world is ours!

90
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:32,621
You don't know
who you're up against!

91
00:11:32,680 --> 00:11:34,659
I'm Tony Montana!

92
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:37,587
- I'm the powerhouse!
- Yeah!

93
00:11:37,680 --> 00:11:38,704
Come here.

94
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:42,579
Shit Colombians,

95
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:44,580
they're everywhere.

96
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:47,547
See, Colombians everywhere.

97
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:53,542
You really looked like Scarface.

98
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:05,580
You were good.

99
00:12:05,680 --> 00:12:07,784
Now it all has to be ours,
the whole world.

100
00:12:08,760 --> 00:12:10,625
Miami, all of it.

101
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:26,699
My friend, got stuff?

102
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:37,783
You got stuff?

103
00:12:42,760 --> 00:12:45,661
- Got good stuff?
- You got money?

104
00:12:45,760 --> 00:12:49,582
- Sure, you got coke?
- What do you want to pay?

105
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:51,705
Me? 50.

106
00:12:53,600 --> 00:12:56,740
- 55, can you do it?
- No, 55 is too much, 50.

107
00:12:57,800 --> 00:12:59,745
You sure?

108
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:02,580
Wait here for me.

109
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:12,777
Where's Smarty?

110
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:31,698
Hey, kid!

111
00:13:44,640 --> 00:13:46,540
Give him the money.

112
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:54,621
- Is it all here?
- Yeah.

113
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:12,542
- Okay?
- Yes.

114
00:14:15,760 --> 00:14:18,661
- Want to see it?
- I want to try it.

115
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:21,783
I gave you the money!

116
00:14:22,640 --> 00:14:23,698
Wait!

117
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,700
Open your hand.

118
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:35,624
It's good.

119
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:39,783
Give me all of it!

120
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:50,545
Grab the money!

121
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:59,625
Giovanni, I brought the kids.

122
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:00,744
Come in.

123
00:16:04,560 --> 00:16:06,744
You know very well why you're here.

124
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:10,740
Too much ruckus going on in my area,
because I'm the boss here.

125
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:12,783
That's just you sayin'.

126
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:16,739
If I had you come here, I know.
No back-talk

127
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:19,704
or I'll smash your face!

128
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:23,746
- What happened?
- For the moment, nothing.

129
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:25,783
Get me?

130
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:30,627
I can't be made to look bad
because of two kids like you.

131
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:33,740
The next time
I hear anything about you,

132
00:16:34,560 --> 00:16:35,743
I'll blow your heads off.

133
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:39,580
- If it's like you say...
- Shut up when I'm talking.

134
00:16:39,680 --> 00:16:41,705
Then if I come to realize

135
00:16:42,680 --> 00:16:44,705
you're worth something,

136
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:47,587
which I'll determine and I'll decide,

137
00:16:47,760 --> 00:16:50,547
you can work for me.

138
00:16:50,720 --> 00:16:52,699
Is that clear?

139
00:16:53,760 --> 00:16:55,580
Show them out.

140
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:03,585
"I'll smash your face!"

141
00:17:03,680 --> 00:17:05,705
And I'll tear your beard!

142
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:08,540
Without a T-shirt.

143
00:17:08,640 --> 00:17:10,665
"Sweet Pea", looked like a bum.

144
00:17:11,720 --> 00:17:12,744
A real bum.

145
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:16,746
He is a bum! Did you see
who he sent to get us?

146
00:17:17,720 --> 00:17:19,699
If that guy's the boss here,

147
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:21,745
then here we can be the bosses.

148
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:26,660
If a guy like him is boss here,
this area is ours!

149
00:17:27,640 --> 00:17:29,585
I'll live for 30 years
if he's boss here.

150
00:17:30,760 --> 00:17:33,581
Sure, because he's a retard!

151
00:17:33,760 --> 00:17:37,662
Get it? I'II live for 30 years.

152
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:40,542
But he could at least shave!

153
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:41,698
Shave!

154
00:17:42,680 --> 00:17:44,625
"I'll smash your face!"

155
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:47,704
Let's go have a snort to spite him.

156
00:17:48,640 --> 00:17:51,586
We've got everything,
we can do like we want.

157
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:57,581
Anyway, he's a fat shit-ass.

158
00:17:57,760 --> 00:17:59,625
He bugged you?

159
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:01,745
He showers once a week!

160
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:07,705
"I'll blow your heads off!"

161
00:18:31,760 --> 00:18:32,784
Roberto!

162
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:44,619
Let's go, it's too small.

163
00:18:44,720 --> 00:18:48,588
- But the methane one's big.
- No, it's small.

164
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:52,748
- Can I finish measuring?
- No, we're wasting time.

165
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:59,628
- I have to take some shots.
- What a bore with these pictures!

166
00:18:59,760 --> 00:19:01,580
Let's go!

167
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:08,620
Just look at this.

168
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:11,585
It's disgusting down there.

169
00:19:20,560 --> 00:19:21,697
Here is perfect.

170
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:24,540
It's perfect.

171
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:27,780
We're near the highway,
the trucks can get really close,

172
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:31,546
they dump the earth
and cover all the water.

173
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:32,744
Perfect.

174
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:36,779
Franco, it's 85 meters.

175
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:39,545
Get the length too.

176
00:19:41,720 --> 00:19:43,585
Come here.

177
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:47,584
Dante.

178
00:19:47,720 --> 00:19:49,665
Hello, everything okay?

179
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:53,745
This is Roberto.

180
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:59,746
- It's time we made room for youth.
- We need new energy.

181
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:01,745
Take a few more shots.

182
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:05,625
Did you hear?

183
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:07,699
They bombed me,

184
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:09,665
at the cement plant.

185
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:12,779
A whole wall came down,

186
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:14,658
slowly.

187
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,665
Be careful.

188
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:18,705
Zio resolved it.

189
00:20:19,560 --> 00:20:22,586
I'd forgotten to pay
for some land I'd bought.

190
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:25,621
- An injunction against payment?
- Yeah!

191
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:27,785
- What do you think?
- It's fine.

192
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:32,622
- Can we fill this quarry?
- Sure can.

193
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:34,665
Tell Zio it's fine.

194
00:20:34,760 --> 00:20:38,708
Remember, everything clean:
Terracing, solid stuff...

195
00:20:39,720 --> 00:20:42,700
Or the redevelopment agency
will break our balls.

196
00:20:43,600 --> 00:20:46,740
Don't worry,
you emptied it and I'll fill it.

197
00:20:55,800 --> 00:20:59,702
All the pieces have to be cut
and the sizes worked out.

198
00:21:01,680 --> 00:21:03,659
They want 120 of these.

199
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:17,699
Six and seven are identical.

200
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:23,705
Here the satin is cut on the bias.

201
00:21:23,800 --> 00:21:25,700
It's all hand-hemmed.

202
00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:27,665
Is it tough?

203
00:21:27,760 --> 00:21:30,706
The models aren't hard,
I can do it.

204
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:35,784
Eight hundred items in two months,
is our request.

205
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:39,546
Keep in mind
we start at 50 Euros per item.

206
00:21:40,720 --> 00:21:43,700
You've seen the models,
the price is good,

207
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:46,587
estimate and make your offers.

208
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:49,785
Thirty Euro, 30 days?

209
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:52,579
Don't go any lower.

210
00:21:52,720 --> 00:21:54,699
This is high fashion,
it's not pret-a-porter.

211
00:21:54,760 --> 00:21:56,705
Forty-five, in two months.

212
00:21:58,680 --> 00:22:00,705
- Ms. Zamarion!
- Yes?

213
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:02,779
Thirty-eight, forty.

214
00:22:03,600 --> 00:22:05,625
That's a very interesting proposal.

215
00:22:05,720 --> 00:22:07,620
Thirty-five, thirty-five,

216
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:10,666
excellent workmanship
and delivery times respected.

217
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:13,700
Thirty, thirty!

218
00:22:21,560 --> 00:22:22,697
Please,

219
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:25,542
we're not imposing anything!

220
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:28,659
Did we say thirty, thirty?

221
00:22:29,760 --> 00:22:31,660
At this point

222
00:22:31,760 --> 00:22:33,660
twenty-eight, thirty!

223
00:22:37,720 --> 00:22:39,620
Thirty, twenty-five!

224
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:43,665
I can't lose this bid.

225
00:22:44,800 --> 00:22:46,779
Come here, there's some bubbly!

226
00:22:49,680 --> 00:22:51,580
Are they coming?

227
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:53,784
- I don't think so.
- Why not?

228
00:22:56,720 --> 00:22:59,541
Five days less for delivery,

229
00:22:59,640 --> 00:23:02,541
we'll have to work overtime,
and I'II do nights...

230
00:23:02,640 --> 00:23:04,619
What's odd about that?

231
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:06,665
They're talking overtime pay.

232
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:08,705
They'II get it!

233
00:23:08,760 --> 00:23:11,706
Am I scared of a little overtime?

234
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:15,580
Like the last time?

235
00:23:15,640 --> 00:23:17,699
Don't worry,
this time it's a sure thing.

236
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:23,667
- They've lost their trust.
- I know.

237
00:23:23,760 --> 00:23:27,662
- I asked you to talk to them.
- You do it, please.

238
00:23:27,760 --> 00:23:30,706
You're on closer terms,
they respect you.

239
00:23:31,720 --> 00:23:33,665
Do me this favor.

240
00:23:34,760 --> 00:23:36,739
Don't say no, go talk to them.

241
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:39,700
You know I'm fond of you,

242
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:41,745
I'll have to make
a gold statue to you!

243
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:44,587
I'll go down and see the accountant
for the money.

244
00:23:49,760 --> 00:23:52,581
Sorry, how much is this?

245
00:23:53,560 --> 00:23:54,663
Ten thousand.

246
00:23:56,640 --> 00:23:58,665
It's not enough, I need more.

247
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:00,703
Twice that at least.

248
00:24:01,560 --> 00:24:03,585
Mr. Enzo,
you're already "complicated".

249
00:24:03,680 --> 00:24:05,705
Yes, but for personal affairs.

250
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:08,587
I need this for work.

251
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:10,705
I'II give it back in three months.

252
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:13,587
But this isn't enough.

253
00:24:13,680 --> 00:24:15,739
If you don't need it
and it's not enough,

254
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:17,743
I'll take it back.

255
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:19,703
It's best for you.

256
00:24:20,560 --> 00:24:22,619
Don't be like that, listen,

257
00:24:22,720 --> 00:24:24,745
I need at least double!

258
00:24:25,680 --> 00:24:27,545
It's no risk,

259
00:24:27,640 --> 00:24:28,743
you'll earn from it, right?

260
00:24:29,600 --> 00:24:30,658
What can I say?

261
00:24:30,760 --> 00:24:33,581
I'll pass it on,
can you make-do for now?

262
00:24:33,720 --> 00:24:35,665
Yes, I'II take it.

263
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:48,619
Congratulations, Mr. Pasquale.

264
00:24:48,680 --> 00:24:49,738
Thank you.

265
00:24:50,560 --> 00:24:51,743
We met yesterday.

266
00:24:53,560 --> 00:24:55,699
I need your help.

267
00:25:02,720 --> 00:25:04,745
I am having trouble with work.

268
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:09,701
I have to get into
haute couture right away,

269
00:25:11,680 --> 00:25:13,625
but for me

270
00:25:14,600 --> 00:25:16,579
it is very difficult.

271
00:25:16,640 --> 00:25:18,665
I need help.

272
00:25:21,760 --> 00:25:23,705
You are

273
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:26,579
a great master,

274
00:25:26,720 --> 00:25:28,779
you are very important for me.

275
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:31,545
You teach ten lessons

276
00:25:31,760 --> 00:25:34,547
to workers in my factory.

277
00:25:35,720 --> 00:25:37,745
I pay you in cash,

278
00:25:38,760 --> 00:25:40,739
2,000 Euros a lesson

279
00:25:42,640 --> 00:25:43,777
for ten lessons.

280
00:25:44,720 --> 00:25:47,780
We work together,
but no one knows it,

281
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:50,700
just the two of us.

282
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:54,585
I need your help.

283
00:25:55,760 --> 00:25:57,580
Think it over.

284
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:04,627
- What's the cloth like?
- Come and see.

285
00:26:38,560 --> 00:26:39,697
I've got nothin'!

286
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:41,745
Don't move!

287
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:47,701
They must have gone over to his side,

288
00:27:48,560 --> 00:27:51,586
or they'd hsve arrested
me first and then those other guys.

289
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:54,746
Believe me? All of them were there
when I called you.

290
00:27:54,800 --> 00:27:57,587
I said: Check out this car,
it's suspect.

291
00:27:57,680 --> 00:27:59,625
This stuff here is ours.

292
00:27:59,760 --> 00:28:01,625
My gun!

293
00:28:03,600 --> 00:28:06,546
Check this stuff out,
there should be fifty-six.

294
00:28:08,600 --> 00:28:10,659
Good, Toto, this is for you.

295
00:28:14,760 --> 00:28:16,785
How can I get working with you?

296
00:28:17,600 --> 00:28:19,579
We'll let you know.

297
00:28:21,560 --> 00:28:23,744
- Did you turn off the water?
- Of course!

298
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:26,739
- Can I help out?
- No, you'll get wet.

299
00:28:27,600 --> 00:28:28,703
Doesn't matter!

300
00:28:29,640 --> 00:28:31,540
Come and see.

301
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:33,585
Careful not to slip.

302
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:38,588
- Is it coming from the well?
- No, I think it's from the pipe.

303
00:28:38,760 --> 00:28:41,627
Careful, water's coming in.

304
00:28:42,760 --> 00:28:45,547
See if you can close it.

305
00:28:45,640 --> 00:28:47,665
It's closed,
but it's the pipe that...

306
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:55,779
I'd give you a hand, but...

307
00:28:57,640 --> 00:28:58,743
What a great day!

308
00:28:59,560 --> 00:29:01,585
Push it all in one direction.

309
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:10,541
I thought I'd be having coffee!

310
00:29:10,640 --> 00:29:13,700
- Nice coffee, huh?
- I'll have some next time.

311
00:29:21,640 --> 00:29:23,585
Totore, things okay?

312
00:29:24,800 --> 00:29:27,701
- Can I say hi?
- No, you gotta leave.

313
00:29:27,800 --> 00:29:30,542
Go down with these bags!

314
00:29:31,640 --> 00:29:33,585
You have to move!

315
00:29:34,680 --> 00:29:36,659
Ma'am, go around the other way.

316
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:39,666
- What's going on?
- Everything's fine, leave.

317
00:29:59,720 --> 00:30:00,744
Lucia?

318
00:30:31,640 --> 00:30:32,698
Come closer.

319
00:30:33,720 --> 00:30:36,541
- What's your nsme?
- Luigi.

320
00:30:37,760 --> 00:30:40,581
- Are you scared?
- No.

321
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:42,739
- Sure?
- No.

322
00:30:43,600 --> 00:30:44,737
We'll see.

323
00:30:45,760 --> 00:30:48,706
- Are you strong?
- Yeah!

324
00:30:49,680 --> 00:30:51,705
Let's see how strong you are.

325
00:30:55,680 --> 00:30:57,625
Why are you shaking?

326
00:30:58,800 --> 00:31:00,540
No?

327
00:33:01,720 --> 00:33:04,621
- See how strong this kid is.
- Come closer!

328
00:33:11,800 --> 00:33:14,587
- Are you scared?
- Yes.

329
00:33:31,680 --> 00:33:33,580
Now you're a man.

330
00:33:51,760 --> 00:33:53,739
Nothin'! Everything's okay!

331
00:33:54,800 --> 00:33:58,622
When I did my piercing,
I got an infection.

332
00:33:58,720 --> 00:34:00,585
Let's see.

333
00:34:01,600 --> 00:34:03,579
You went and did it there?

334
00:34:04,760 --> 00:34:07,627
- I'd like to have it on my eyebrow.
- Stinks.

335
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:09,699
It's nicer there, you're right.

336
00:34:11,800 --> 00:34:13,745
It's gonna rain.

337
00:34:19,640 --> 00:34:20,698
Everything's okay!

338
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:22,779
A car's coming!

339
00:34:24,720 --> 00:34:26,620
It went in!

340
00:34:28,720 --> 00:34:30,665
It's going in!

341
00:34:31,600 --> 00:34:33,579
Check out this other one!

342
00:34:35,760 --> 00:34:37,660
Everything's okay!

343
00:35:08,720 --> 00:35:11,700
Sorry I'm late, the Councilman,
City Hall, the traffic...

344
00:35:12,640 --> 00:35:14,699
- My father.
- How do you do.

345
00:35:18,640 --> 00:35:21,586
I'm glad he's with you
you're a good person.

346
00:35:21,720 --> 00:35:23,699
He's in your care.

347
00:35:23,800 --> 00:35:25,700
He's a clever guy.

348
00:35:27,600 --> 00:35:28,737
I don't doubt that but...

349
00:35:28,840 --> 00:35:31,661
- Having work is important to him.
- Of course.

350
00:35:31,720 --> 00:35:34,621
I tried so hard
to find him work in Naples...

351
00:35:34,720 --> 00:35:37,746
- Where do you work?
- In the hospital, intensive care.

352
00:35:38,600 --> 00:35:40,625
A bad division.

353
00:35:41,680 --> 00:35:45,741
I tried to get him in,
but I have no connections.

354
00:35:46,600 --> 00:35:48,579
He's all set now.

355
00:35:48,680 --> 00:35:51,581
You did something no one else did.

356
00:35:51,680 --> 00:35:53,739
I thank you, you raised him well.

357
00:35:53,840 --> 00:35:55,740
Have you always worked in Naples?

358
00:35:56,560 --> 00:35:58,619
No, also in Trieste, Udine,

359
00:35:59,560 --> 00:36:01,619
- Venice...
- That's where we're going.

360
00:36:01,720 --> 00:36:04,666
I told him about Venice.

361
00:36:05,640 --> 00:36:08,746
He's excited, it's his first time.

362
00:36:09,600 --> 00:36:12,740
Dad, we have a plane.

363
00:36:13,560 --> 00:36:15,585
Did you bring some things?

364
00:36:15,720 --> 00:36:17,745
What's that, your gym bag?

365
00:36:18,760 --> 00:36:21,627
- Goodbye.
- He's in your care.

366
00:36:40,760 --> 00:36:44,582
- What do you pay for disposal?
- Today I'm paying 50.

367
00:36:44,680 --> 00:36:45,783
Your offer?

368
00:36:46,640 --> 00:36:48,585
We can halve your costs,

369
00:36:48,680 --> 00:36:50,580
25 cents a kilo.

370
00:36:50,680 --> 00:36:52,580
That's good,

371
00:36:52,680 --> 00:36:54,659
but is it all "clean",
like they say in the United States?

372
00:36:54,720 --> 00:36:56,665
Since it's toxic waste,

373
00:36:56,760 --> 00:36:59,547
certification,
storage and transportation.

374
00:37:01,760 --> 00:37:04,706
- Is there a contract to look over?
- Of course.

375
00:37:08,720 --> 00:37:10,620
In case you're wondering,

376
00:37:10,720 --> 00:37:12,699
the disposal cycle

377
00:37:12,800 --> 00:37:15,587
goes to the dispossl area
in Marcianise.

378
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:17,585
I'm telling you in fairness.

379
00:37:17,680 --> 00:37:19,739
Thank you for the information,

380
00:37:20,600 --> 00:37:22,784
but my only concern
is that it's "clean".

381
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:25,625
You can rest assured of that.

382
00:37:25,720 --> 00:37:27,699
We can dispose of all the waste

383
00:37:27,840 --> 00:37:29,785
that you produce in a year.

384
00:37:30,600 --> 00:37:31,703
Eight hundred tons.

385
00:37:33,560 --> 00:37:34,584
It's not a problem.

386
00:37:34,680 --> 00:37:35,783
That's a lot.

387
00:37:39,840 --> 00:37:41,785
My concern is disposal.

388
00:37:42,600 --> 00:37:44,739
We serve various companies,
you can check.

389
00:37:45,760 --> 00:37:47,705
I already have!

390
00:37:48,720 --> 00:37:50,620
Don't worry.

391
00:37:51,760 --> 00:37:54,661
As far as I can see,
there's maximum transparency.

392
00:37:54,720 --> 00:37:56,540
Absolutely.

393
00:37:58,720 --> 00:38:01,746
- The warehouses at Teverola?
- We use them for tires.

394
00:38:02,600 --> 00:38:03,624
Exactly.

395
00:38:03,800 --> 00:38:06,701
Will we put the tannery waste
in the quarry?

396
00:38:06,800 --> 00:38:09,542
- Don't talk foolishness.
- Where then?

397
00:38:09,640 --> 00:38:11,665
Check the European catalogue.

398
00:38:13,720 --> 00:38:15,620
Here they are,04.

399
00:38:16,600 --> 00:38:18,739
The ones in red,
are among the most dangerous.

400
00:38:19,600 --> 00:38:22,706
"Exhausted degreasing baths
with solvents, no liquid phase."

401
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:24,777
No, no good.

402
00:38:26,720 --> 00:38:28,699
Then 4-11:

403
00:38:28,760 --> 00:38:31,627
"Waste containing halogenated
compounds from operations

404
00:38:31,720 --> 00:38:33,665
of manufacturing and finishing."

405
00:38:33,760 --> 00:38:35,660
These are good.

406
00:38:35,760 --> 00:38:39,537
It's stuff the earth absorbs,
we'll mix it with compost.

407
00:38:39,640 --> 00:38:40,698
Fertilizer!

408
00:38:43,600 --> 00:38:46,546
All that leaves is
Milan's sweeping refuse,

409
00:38:46,640 --> 00:38:48,540
that's 60 trucks.

410
00:38:49,640 --> 00:38:52,541
- The quarries at San Felice?
- They're too small.

411
00:38:52,640 --> 00:38:54,585
I don't think so, look.

412
00:38:54,800 --> 00:38:56,665
Let me see.

413
00:39:02,680 --> 00:39:04,739
They're too small
and they're shallow,

414
00:39:05,800 --> 00:39:07,665
they're no good.

415
00:39:18,800 --> 00:39:22,577
Yes... I've got
ten contracts out of ten.

416
00:39:26,600 --> 00:39:27,703
Is he near you?

417
00:39:30,560 --> 00:39:31,663
Put him on.

418
00:39:32,560 --> 00:39:33,697
I'll talk to him.

419
00:39:55,760 --> 00:39:58,581
I told him, everything's okay.

420
00:40:11,680 --> 00:40:14,581
- Do you like traveling?
- Sure!

421
00:40:14,840 --> 00:40:16,740
We'll take more trips.

422
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:27,739
Everyone here works in boats?

423
00:40:28,600 --> 00:40:31,580
Everyone, firemen, ambulances...

424
00:40:32,720 --> 00:40:35,746
- Funerals.
- I've already seen two.

425
00:40:36,600 --> 00:40:38,579
Even the dead go by boat!

426
00:41:00,760 --> 00:41:02,739
Wow, they've got so many!

427
00:41:08,600 --> 00:41:09,624
Steady me.

428
00:41:59,720 --> 00:42:01,620
There's nothing here.

429
00:42:15,800 --> 00:42:17,700
Nothing?

430
00:42:17,800 --> 00:42:19,665
Are you sure?

431
00:42:44,800 --> 00:42:46,620
Oh God!

432
00:42:46,680 --> 00:42:48,625
Look what's here!

433
00:42:55,680 --> 00:42:57,705
See? It's like you said!

434
00:43:00,720 --> 00:43:02,585
Look here!

435
00:43:02,720 --> 00:43:04,585
A Beretta 93!

436
00:43:04,680 --> 00:43:06,545
A Kalashnikov!

437
00:43:06,760 --> 00:43:08,739
See if they're loaded.

438
00:43:09,680 --> 00:43:11,739
- Check.
- It's unloaded.

439
00:43:26,680 --> 00:43:28,580
Look, an M12!

440
00:43:28,800 --> 00:43:30,745
This is the 921.

441
00:43:31,560 --> 00:43:32,663
That bearded bum!

442
00:43:32,760 --> 00:43:34,785
We'll see how
he blows my head off!

443
00:43:35,840 --> 00:43:38,786
Enough for Casale di Principe!
Everybody!

444
00:43:40,600 --> 00:43:42,625
Won't blow my head off now, eh?

445
00:43:46,800 --> 00:43:48,745
Should I put two in?

446
00:43:50,720 --> 00:43:52,620
And Nikita's?

447
00:43:52,720 --> 00:43:54,620
And the 38?

448
00:44:10,680 --> 00:44:13,740
- Want to see how I can shoot?
- Show me!

449
00:44:14,760 --> 00:44:16,625
Show me!

450
00:44:17,680 --> 00:44:19,625
Aim there!

451
00:44:53,800 --> 00:44:55,620
I hit it!

452
00:45:11,640 --> 00:45:13,665
We'll blow
the Colombians' heads off!

453
00:45:21,760 --> 00:45:23,625
That's good.

454
00:45:27,800 --> 00:45:29,665
Everything okay?

455
00:45:34,680 --> 00:45:36,625
With love and feeling.

456
00:45:49,600 --> 00:45:51,739
- What is it?
- Your wife's on the phone.

457
00:45:52,600 --> 00:45:53,783
Tell her not to wait up.

458
00:45:54,600 --> 00:45:56,739
Don't get tired out, need anything?

459
00:45:57,600 --> 00:45:58,703
No, thanks.

460
00:45:58,800 --> 00:46:00,779
- You'll lock up?
- Yes.

461
00:46:01,680 --> 00:46:02,704
Goodnight.

462
00:46:25,800 --> 00:46:27,620
Xian?

463
00:47:01,640 --> 00:47:02,743
I have been waiting for you.

464
00:47:04,800 --> 00:47:07,780
- I got lost.
- I am happy you came.

465
00:47:21,600 --> 00:47:22,658
Please sit down.

466
00:47:25,680 --> 00:47:27,705
We are cooking fish.

467
00:47:37,640 --> 00:47:39,585
I've already eaten.

468
00:47:40,640 --> 00:47:42,665
Try a typical Chinese dish.

469
00:47:43,600 --> 00:47:44,703
Okay?

470
00:47:50,760 --> 00:47:53,627
Just cooked, it is good.

471
00:47:53,680 --> 00:47:55,580
Meat with bell peppers.

472
00:47:55,680 --> 00:47:57,625
I've already eaten.

473
00:48:00,680 --> 00:48:01,738
Taste.

474
00:48:02,600 --> 00:48:04,545
We use chopsticks.

475
00:48:04,640 --> 00:48:06,665
- I don't know how to use them.
- Try!

476
00:48:09,680 --> 00:48:11,625
I am pleased,

477
00:48:11,680 --> 00:48:13,705
we have a little toast.

478
00:48:14,800 --> 00:48:17,542
We go to the factory.

479
00:48:24,800 --> 00:48:26,665
Why not?

480
00:48:30,680 --> 00:48:32,625
I put a pillow in here.

481
00:48:32,760 --> 00:48:34,625
It's dangerous.

482
00:48:35,760 --> 00:48:39,582
I already told you,
no one can know, just us.

483
00:48:39,760 --> 00:48:41,739
It's better for both of us.

484
00:48:42,600 --> 00:48:46,627
- Won't I need air?
- No, there's an opening.

485
00:48:47,680 --> 00:48:50,626
I'll open the front window,
so air will come in.

486
00:48:52,680 --> 00:48:54,545
Forgive me.

487
00:48:56,600 --> 00:48:57,783
Are we sure?

488
00:48:59,760 --> 00:49:02,786
It is best for both of us,
because it is dangerous.

489
00:49:05,760 --> 00:49:08,581
- Does air come through here?
- Yes.

490
00:49:08,800 --> 00:49:10,779
And I'II open the window too.

491
00:50:13,600 --> 00:50:15,579
Please come in, Mr. Pasquale.

492
00:50:16,800 --> 00:50:18,745
All are waiting for you.

493
00:50:21,720 --> 00:50:23,665
All are very happy.

494
00:50:38,600 --> 00:50:40,739
I told them who you are
and all are happy.

495
00:50:43,640 --> 00:50:45,540
What a nice factory!

496
00:50:45,720 --> 00:50:47,745
More than 80 people.

497
00:51:29,720 --> 00:51:31,665
I'm moved.

498
00:51:35,680 --> 00:51:37,625
What can I say?

499
00:51:38,760 --> 00:51:40,739
To do this work

500
00:51:41,800 --> 00:51:44,542
you need lots of patience...

501
00:51:49,800 --> 00:51:51,700
... and lots of love.

502
00:51:57,760 --> 00:51:59,705
For the first lesson...

503
00:52:02,640 --> 00:52:04,665
... I'II cut out a bodice.

504
00:52:12,680 --> 00:52:13,738
Let's begin.

505
00:52:24,680 --> 00:52:27,581
You must place patterns carefully.

506
00:52:33,760 --> 00:52:35,739
Spread the cloth well...

507
00:52:58,680 --> 00:53:00,625
Maria, are you asleep?

508
00:53:05,640 --> 00:53:07,699
Where have I been, in China?

509
00:53:10,680 --> 00:53:12,659
They were all bowing to me.

510
00:53:14,760 --> 00:53:16,580
Master!

511
00:53:16,720 --> 00:53:19,587
They called me "master"!

512
00:53:24,600 --> 00:53:27,580
- Did you know the Chinese can cook?
- The Chinese?

513
00:53:27,720 --> 00:53:29,665
Darn right!

514
00:53:29,800 --> 00:53:32,587
They cooked a delicious bass!

515
00:53:36,600 --> 00:53:37,783
There were boxes everywhere

516
00:53:38,600 --> 00:53:40,579
and they put me in the trunk!

517
00:53:41,720 --> 00:53:43,699
Both coming and going.

518
00:53:47,600 --> 00:53:48,783
I need some sleep.

519
00:53:52,600 --> 00:53:53,658
Here.

520
00:53:54,600 --> 00:53:56,625
I have to sleep a few hours.

521
00:54:00,640 --> 00:54:02,665
What's this money?

522
00:54:13,680 --> 00:54:15,625
Where did you get it?

523
00:54:15,760 --> 00:54:17,705
I have to sleep.

524
00:54:20,680 --> 00:54:22,580
Help me understand.

525
00:54:22,680 --> 00:54:24,705
I talked to my son this morning,

526
00:54:24,800 --> 00:54:27,587
he said: "Mom I'm leaving,

527
00:54:27,800 --> 00:54:29,745
I'm going to be a secessionist."

528
00:54:30,800 --> 00:54:32,620
Really?

529
00:54:36,640 --> 00:54:38,585
What did you say?

530
00:54:38,760 --> 00:54:40,660
He's convinced,

531
00:54:41,640 --> 00:54:43,665
he said: "We're great,

532
00:54:43,760 --> 00:54:47,662
we'll win the war,
the others are nobodies".

533
00:54:47,720 --> 00:54:50,746
War? A bunch of morons
warring against us?

534
00:54:51,680 --> 00:54:53,625
You have to stop him.

535
00:54:54,760 --> 00:54:56,705
This side is the right side.

536
00:54:58,600 --> 00:55:00,659
Have you seen what's happening?

537
00:55:00,800 --> 00:55:02,745
There are killings every day.

538
00:55:04,640 --> 00:55:07,586
Don't say anything to anybody,
not even your husband.

539
00:55:08,760 --> 00:55:10,705
Who'd ever tell him!

540
00:55:12,760 --> 00:55:15,740
When he gets out, what'll he do?
Father and son will kill each other?

541
00:55:16,600 --> 00:55:18,625
No, because your son
will stay right here.

542
00:55:20,720 --> 00:55:22,745
