I can't consider them kids anymore.

808
01:24:24,720 --> 01:24:26,699
They have to die, that's final!

809
01:24:26,800 --> 01:24:30,668
You're right,
but first let's tell the families.

810
01:24:30,760 --> 01:24:32,705
I don't know who they are.

811
01:24:34,720 --> 01:24:37,666
Will you take care of it?

812
01:24:37,800 --> 01:24:39,825
I'll handle it!

813
01:25:07,600 --> 01:25:08,783
Toto, is that you?

814
01:25:14,840 --> 01:25:17,786
- What happened to Silvana?
- In the storeroom.

815
01:25:33,840 --> 01:25:36,627
How come it's so dark?

816
01:25:36,720 --> 01:25:38,665
Why are you in the dark?

817
01:25:38,720 --> 01:25:40,585
It's okay like this.

818
01:25:40,840 --> 01:25:42,660
Your change.

819
01:25:44,800 --> 01:25:47,701
- The bread?
- There wasn't any.

820
01:25:47,800 --> 01:25:50,701
- What'll we eat?
- There's pasta.

821
01:25:53,720 --> 01:25:56,587
- Take your change.
- It's for you.

822
01:26:06,720 --> 01:26:08,824
Why did you put her
in the storeroom?

823
01:26:09,680 --> 01:26:11,625
She's fine where she is.

824
01:26:11,840 --> 01:26:14,661
She's just an animal!

825
01:27:25,720 --> 01:27:27,745
Come here a minute,
I have to talk to you.

826
01:27:29,680 --> 01:27:31,625
Don't come out, it's dangerous.

827
01:27:31,760 --> 01:27:33,785
Come on, no one can see you.

828
01:27:37,720 --> 01:27:39,665
What are you doing, you're going?

829
01:27:42,800 --> 01:27:44,586
Listen to me!

830
01:27:44,840 --> 01:27:47,627
They said I have to leave.

831
01:27:47,800 --> 01:27:49,779
I have to leave my house.

832
01:27:50,720 --> 01:27:52,665
I can't do anything.

833
01:27:52,760 --> 01:27:54,705
I'm not leaving!

834
01:27:55,720 --> 01:27:57,665
Come here a minute!

835
01:28:03,720 --> 01:28:06,780
Tell those friends of yours,
I'm not leaving!

836
01:28:08,640 --> 01:28:10,699
Tell those nice people!

837
01:28:10,800 --> 01:28:14,622
I won't betray my son
and I'm not moving from here!

838
01:28:16,680 --> 01:28:18,659
Not coming in for coffee?

839
01:28:18,720 --> 01:28:20,585
Run off, run away!

840
01:28:59,640 --> 01:29:00,777
Hello, accountant.

841
01:29:01,680 --> 01:29:02,704
Please come in.

842
01:29:03,840 --> 01:29:06,786
Why this sudden call?

843
01:29:07,600 --> 01:29:08,737
You're worrying me.

844
01:29:09,600 --> 01:29:11,625
The designers pay me after 60 days,

845
01:29:11,720 --> 01:29:13,745
I have a little money,

846
01:29:13,840 --> 01:29:16,582
but this wasn't the agreement.

847
01:29:16,680 --> 01:29:18,705
Money isn't the problem.

848
01:29:19,800 --> 01:29:21,665
What is it then?

849
01:29:21,760 --> 01:29:23,660
It seems

850
01:29:24,720 --> 01:29:26,745
the problem is in your own house.

851
01:29:27,800 --> 01:29:29,700
In my house?

852
01:29:29,800 --> 01:29:31,745
What problem is it?

853
01:29:32,840 --> 01:29:34,740
One of your associates,

854
01:29:36,600 --> 01:29:37,658
Pasquale Del Prete,

855
01:29:37,800 --> 01:29:39,620
has sold out to the Chinese.

856
01:29:49,760 --> 01:29:51,625
We're done.

857
01:29:55,600 --> 01:29:56,737
The finishing touches...

858
01:30:05,680 --> 01:30:07,625
I never doubted.

859
01:30:26,760 --> 01:30:28,625
Everything okay?

860
01:30:31,720 --> 01:30:34,746
Remember the first time
I put you to work in the factory?

861
01:30:34,840 --> 01:30:36,740
You were just a kid.

862
01:30:38,800 --> 01:30:39,824
Right.

863
01:30:49,720 --> 01:30:51,779
- Everything alright?
- Yes.

864
01:31:15,640 --> 01:31:18,700
Tell him to go slower, not too fast.

865
01:31:32,680 --> 01:31:33,783
Well done, Giulia.

866
01:31:34,680 --> 01:31:35,738
She's good.

867
01:32:06,680 --> 01:32:08,659
In the morning I do Tai Chi.

868
01:32:08,760 --> 01:32:09,738
Really?

869
01:32:10,600 --> 01:32:12,818
- It's nice.
- It is good for your health.

870
01:32:13,680 --> 01:32:15,705
It is like in China.

871
01:32:16,720 --> 01:32:20,622
When you go to the park
in the morning, it is full of people

872
01:32:21,760 --> 01:32:23,660
old people too.

873
01:32:24,640 --> 01:32:26,619
All doing Tai Chi.

874
01:32:26,720 --> 01:32:27,823
Everyone

875
01:32:28,840 --> 01:32:31,627
likes the culture of Tai Chi.

876
01:32:33,640 --> 01:32:35,779
It's a tradition of Chinese culture.

877
01:32:36,640 --> 01:32:38,699
When will you do egg rolls for me?

878
01:33:32,800 --> 01:33:34,620
Wait up.

879
01:33:36,640 --> 01:33:39,746
I spoke to the doctors,
you'll soon be released.

880
01:33:46,720 --> 01:33:48,665
Damn you,

881
01:33:48,800 --> 01:33:50,700
you really goofed up.

882
01:33:52,760 --> 01:33:56,628
They loved the models,
they've asked for more...

883
01:33:56,720 --> 01:33:58,620
You knew everything.

884
01:33:58,720 --> 01:34:00,779
That's how I saved your life.

885
01:34:01,760 --> 01:34:04,627
Those people don't kid around.

886
01:34:04,760 --> 01:34:06,625
Leave me alone.

887
01:34:06,720 --> 01:34:10,622
You should thank me,
those guys will kill you.

888
01:34:10,680 --> 01:34:12,705
You and I pulled through.

889
01:34:12,800 --> 01:34:15,780
- Find another tailor.
- Why do you say that?

890
01:34:16,640 --> 01:34:19,666
- I want to be alone.
- How can I do this without you?

891
01:34:19,760 --> 01:34:21,660
I really don't care.

892
01:34:21,760 --> 01:34:25,628
- After all I've done for you.
- What have you done for me?

893
01:34:25,720 --> 01:34:28,780
I took you off the streets,
I fed you for years.

894
01:34:29,600 --> 01:34:32,580
- You've used me since I was a kid.
- Don't say that!

895
01:34:33,720 --> 01:34:36,826
When you're better,
come see me, I'll give you a raise.

896
01:34:38,840 --> 01:34:42,662
Rosa, give me that bike,
I have to go.

897
01:36:07,840 --> 01:36:09,819
No admittance here,

898
01:36:10,640 --> 01:36:11,777
that's it.

899
01:36:25,840 --> 01:36:27,785
Want to give up?

900
01:36:28,640 --> 01:36:30,744
Are we meat for the slaughter house?

901
01:36:39,600 --> 01:36:41,579
Let's shoot,
we'll rack up corpses too.

902
01:36:41,720 --> 01:36:42,778
Corpses?

903
01:36:43,800 --> 01:36:47,577
- I'm not moving without orders.
- What orders?

904
01:36:47,720 --> 01:36:49,745
We don't know how to move.

905
01:36:51,760 --> 01:36:53,705
We don't know anything.

906
01:36:56,800 --> 01:36:59,587
Do we have to keep taking it?

907
01:36:59,720 --> 01:37:01,779
Do we have to wait for orders?

908
01:37:04,800 --> 01:37:06,745
Let's rack up corpses.

909
01:37:06,840 --> 01:37:10,662
What are we waiting for,
to be put down one by one?

910
01:37:14,640 --> 01:37:16,744
If we don't move, nothing will change

911
01:37:16,840 --> 01:37:18,819
No use feeling depressed.

912
01:37:20,720 --> 01:37:22,745
We all have to be convinced.

913
01:37:22,840 --> 01:37:25,661
But without orders, I'm not moving.

914
01:37:27,840 --> 01:37:29,785
This is open war,

915
01:37:30,600 --> 01:37:32,579
you mustn't think about anyone.

916
01:37:32,720 --> 01:37:35,746
- Who do we kill?
- Let's begin in our area.

917
01:37:36,800 --> 01:37:38,779
From our own stronghold.

918
01:37:39,640 --> 01:37:41,744
We don't know who's with us
and who's against us,

919
01:37:41,840 --> 01:37:43,819
who do we make pay?

920
01:37:44,640 --> 01:37:47,666
Where do you think
the order to kill came from?

921
01:37:47,760 --> 01:37:48,818
Think!

922
01:37:50,640 --> 01:37:52,585
Where did it come from?

923
01:37:52,800 --> 01:37:55,621
- From there of course.
- From our own area.

924
01:37:55,720 --> 01:37:57,665
She betrayed us.

925
01:37:57,760 --> 01:37:59,785
We don't touch women.

926
01:38:00,600 --> 01:38:01,703
Don't yell!

927
01:38:02,720 --> 01:38:04,699
What are you saying?

928
01:38:07,800 --> 01:38:11,702
Don't take it out on someone
no part of this, but the son.

929
01:38:11,840 --> 01:38:15,617
- How do we find him?
- His mother's in our district.

930
01:38:15,680 --> 01:38:17,625
It was her son who killed Gaetano.

931
01:38:17,760 --> 01:38:19,705
Let's think what we'll do.

932
01:38:20,720 --> 01:38:22,745
We could use the kid.

933
01:38:23,640 --> 01:38:25,665
He's the only one who can get to her.

934
01:38:26,800 --> 01:38:28,700
He brings her shopping,

935
01:38:28,800 --> 01:38:30,825
he's in good with the woman...

936
01:38:31,760 --> 01:38:33,739
So, if we have to do it

937
01:38:33,840 --> 01:38:35,785
we'll need his help.

938
01:38:38,640 --> 01:38:40,619
Toto, what do you think you'll do?

939
01:38:41,760 --> 01:38:43,785
Are you with us or against us?

940
01:38:50,640 --> 01:38:52,585
What do you say?

941
01:38:53,760 --> 01:38:55,739
Are you with us or not?

942
01:38:57,640 --> 01:39:00,586
- We'll see what we can do.
- No, "we'll see".

943
01:39:00,680 --> 01:39:02,705
Either you're with us
or you're against us,

944
01:39:03,680 --> 01:39:05,625
one or the other.

945
01:39:05,680 --> 01:39:09,628
If you're against us you can't leave,
we can't trust you.

946
01:39:09,720 --> 01:39:11,779
It can't have been her.

947
01:39:12,720 --> 01:39:14,665
This is our decision,

948
01:39:14,760 --> 01:39:16,705
you have to be with us.

949
01:39:16,800 --> 01:39:19,780
That's what we say,
you don't need to think.

950
01:39:24,720 --> 01:39:26,665
What are you going to do?

951
01:39:27,720 --> 01:39:30,746
- We'll see.
- I said no "we'll see".

952
01:39:46,640 --> 01:39:47,698
Come on down.

953
01:39:47,800 --> 01:39:49,745
I have to tell you something!

954
01:39:51,720 --> 01:39:53,585
No, come down!

955
01:39:54,720 --> 01:39:56,745
Hurry, I have to leave!

956
01:41:33,720 --> 01:41:34,778
Sit down!

957
01:42:11,720 --> 01:42:13,665
You've known me for years,

958
01:42:13,760 --> 01:42:15,785
you know what I've always done.

959
01:42:17,720 --> 01:42:19,585
I brought the money.

960
01:42:19,680 --> 01:42:21,705
I brought it to your family too.

961
01:42:23,680 --> 01:42:25,705
I did it because I was ordered to.

962
01:42:30,680 --> 01:42:32,659
War isn't for me.

963
01:42:32,840 --> 01:42:35,661
But you're in it, know that?

964
01:42:37,720 --> 01:42:38,744
Yes.

965
01:42:38,840 --> 01:42:40,626
So?

966
01:42:40,800 --> 01:42:42,620
You tell me.

967
01:42:42,680 --> 01:42:44,580
What can I tell you?

968
01:42:47,840 --> 01:42:50,627
What did you come here for?

969
01:42:52,640 --> 01:42:53,777
To talk to you.

970
01:42:54,680 --> 01:42:55,783
About what?

971
01:42:59,680 --> 01:43:01,625
I want to save myself.

972
01:43:01,720 --> 01:43:03,779
You'll have to buy your life,

973
01:43:04,640 --> 01:43:06,585
I won't give it to you.

974
01:43:10,800 --> 01:43:12,745
What I did there,

975
01:43:13,760 --> 01:43:15,739
I can do for you here.

976
01:43:16,640 --> 01:43:18,665
We don't need money-carriers,

977
01:43:18,720 --> 01:43:21,780
we have to score,
kill people, and we need money.

978
01:43:22,800 --> 01:43:24,700
You're wasting your time.

979
01:43:27,800 --> 01:43:29,700
You're more dead than alive.

980
01:43:29,800 --> 01:43:32,667
But we were brothers before.

981
01:43:32,760 --> 01:43:33,738
Before!

982
01:43:33,840 --> 01:43:36,741
Then they started
messing around with shit.

983
01:43:41,680 --> 01:43:43,705
Our relatives were good people...

984
01:43:44,680 --> 01:43:46,705
so they killed them!

985
01:43:48,680 --> 01:43:49,783
So, don't come asking

986
01:43:50,640 --> 01:43:51,777
to pass to the other side.

987
01:43:52,640 --> 01:43:54,665
We have to score, kill,

988
01:43:54,760 --> 01:43:56,705
and we need money.

989
01:43:57,640 --> 01:43:58,777
If not, you die,

990
01:43:59,640 --> 01:44:01,619
because you're part of the war.

991
01:44:01,680 --> 01:44:03,659
You bring money and I kill people,

992
01:44:03,800 --> 01:44:06,621
we're the same, you and me,
in this war.

993
01:44:07,760 --> 01:44:09,739
- I understand.
- You understand.

994
01:44:20,640 --> 01:44:21,777
Wait a moment.

995
01:44:51,840 --> 01:44:53,740
Everything okay?

996
01:44:55,840 --> 01:44:57,705
And you?

997
01:45:04,760 --> 01:45:06,625
That's four.

998
01:45:16,800 --> 01:45:18,745
Face on the table!

999
01:45:19,600 --> 01:45:20,783
Done?

1000
01:45:21,760 --> 01:45:22,784
Let's go!

1001
01:45:30,760 --> 01:45:32,580
Come on out!

1002
01:45:32,800 --> 01:45:34,745
Lucky, eh?

1003
01:46:57,720 --> 01:46:59,665
That's poison.

1004
01:47:00,840 --> 01:47:02,819
What'd he say?

1005
01:47:03,640 --> 01:47:06,746
My father wants to say the dumping
you're doing on our land

1006
01:47:07,600 --> 01:47:08,737
isn't garbage.

1007
01:47:09,600 --> 01:47:10,737
It's poison.

1008
01:47:10,840 --> 01:47:12,785
It's not garbage?

1009
01:47:14,640 --> 01:47:15,823
You heard right.

1010
01:47:16,640 --> 01:47:17,777
Don't worry.

1011
01:47:18,640 --> 01:47:21,666
A year's gone by with this dumping?

1012
01:47:22,800 --> 01:47:25,701
So far,
all we've done is pay our debts.

1013
01:47:26,800 --> 01:47:27,824
Just barely.

1014
01:47:28,640 --> 01:47:31,780
- Euro.
- I understand, Don Raffaele.

1015
01:47:34,680 --> 01:47:36,784
Everything costs double in Euro.

1016
01:47:37,720 --> 01:47:38,778
And so?

1017
01:47:40,600 --> 01:47:41,817
We need something more.

1018
01:47:43,720 --> 01:47:46,621
These are the prices,
explain it to your kids,

1019
01:47:46,720 --> 01:47:49,666
if I do it for you,
I have to do it for everyone.

1020
01:47:49,760 --> 01:47:51,705
Don't put me
in a difficult situation.

1021
01:47:51,800 --> 01:47:55,668
Okay, if you give us more,
everyone has to get more.

1022
01:47:55,720 --> 01:47:57,665
So, little can be done.

1023
01:47:57,760 --> 01:47:59,819
But, we barely make ends meet,

1024
01:48:00,640 --> 01:48:02,665
we can't go on like this.

1025
01:48:02,760 --> 01:48:04,705
We were thinking,

1026
01:48:05,800 --> 01:48:08,746
is it possible to do more dumping?

1027
01:48:10,800 --> 01:48:12,620
Euro...

1028
01:48:12,800 --> 01:48:14,779
More dumping?

1029
01:48:15,640 --> 01:48:18,586
We have another piece of land
for other dumping sites.

1030
01:48:18,680 --> 01:48:19,817
Near here?

1031
01:48:20,760 --> 01:48:22,625
Around here.

1032
01:48:22,680 --> 01:48:24,625
More dumping we do,

1033
01:48:24,760 --> 01:48:26,739
faster the ground gets filled.

1034
01:48:26,840 --> 01:48:29,627
You have another piece of land?

1035
01:48:30,640 --> 01:48:32,779
- Near here?
- Further on.

1036
01:48:33,640 --> 01:48:36,620
This other land
would be more convenient,

1037
01:48:36,680 --> 01:48:39,660
it's bigger and trucks
can get in easier.

1038
01:48:40,800 --> 01:48:42,586
But...

1039
01:48:44,600 --> 01:48:46,579
Still 100 Euros per dumping.

1040
01:48:46,680 --> 01:48:48,625
What do you mean 100 Euros!

1041
01:48:48,760 --> 01:48:50,705
Don't speak out of turn.

1042
01:48:50,760 --> 01:48:52,739
- He can't increase!
- Who said so?

1043
01:48:53,640 --> 01:48:55,619
We'll increase the trucks.

1044
01:48:56,720 --> 01:48:59,746
You have to increase
the price of each dumping.

1045
01:49:00,800 --> 01:49:02,665
Want to lose everything?

1046
01:49:02,760 --> 01:49:04,785
They have nowhere else to turn.

1047
01:49:05,600 --> 01:49:06,624
Excuse me.

1048
01:49:06,720 --> 01:49:08,585
Don't worry.

1049
01:49:09,840 --> 01:49:11,785
Alright, now we'll reach...

1050
01:49:16,720 --> 01:49:18,620
an agreement.

1051
01:49:18,720 --> 01:49:20,745
Give him a glass of water.

1052
01:49:20,840 --> 01:49:22,819
I'll do it, don't worry.

1053
01:49:32,640 --> 01:49:33,664
Luca!

1054
01:49:40,760 --> 01:49:42,785
You have to clean up this field!

1055
01:49:43,760 --> 01:49:45,580
I'm not Luca.

1056
01:49:45,720 --> 01:49:47,665
Do a little work.

1057
01:49:47,760 --> 01:49:49,660
My name's Roberto.

1058
01:49:51,760 --> 01:49:53,785
This field is such a mess.

1059
01:49:54,760 --> 01:49:56,625
All such a mess.

1060
01:49:57,680 --> 01:49:58,817
Ma'am, it's raining.

1061
01:50:00,600 --> 01:50:01,703
Should I stop?

1062
01:50:01,840 --> 01:50:03,740
Come out of there.

1063
01:50:06,640 --> 01:50:08,585
I'll take you inside.

1064
01:50:08,840 --> 01:50:10,705
I'll be right along.

1065
01:50:10,840 --> 01:50:12,785
They've made ditches here,

1066
01:50:13,640 --> 01:50:15,619
someone should come

1067
01:50:15,720 --> 01:50:17,665
to fill them.

1068
01:50:30,680 --> 01:50:31,704
Let's go!

1069
01:50:43,760 --> 01:50:45,660
What beautiful peaches, thank you!

1070
01:50:45,760 --> 01:50:47,705
I'll take them to the kids.

1071
01:50:47,840 --> 01:50:49,785
See how beautiful they are!

1072
01:50:50,840 --> 01:50:52,660
Let's go.

1073
01:50:52,840 --> 01:50:54,785
Put them in the car.

1074
01:50:54,840 --> 01:50:56,626
Come on!

1075
01:51:09,680 --> 01:51:11,625
Toss that stuff.

1076
01:51:11,720 --> 01:51:13,745
- What?
- The peaches.

